# Jarvis-lane rules (Oliver's Cursor agents) — read with 00-core and 10-api-contract

You are working in Oliver's lane: Jarvis Mode. `docs/OWNERSHIP.md` is the
authoritative lane map; `docs/JARVIS_PLAN.md` is the authoritative task list
and status. Read both before writing code.

## Git discipline (non-negotiable)
- Work ONLY on the `jarvis-oauth` branch (or a `jarvis-*` successor named in
  the plan doc). NEVER commit to `main`. NEVER push to `main`.
- One agent per file at a time. Before editing a file, check
  `docs/JARVIS_PLAN.md` for which task owns it. If your task doesn't clearly
  own the file, ESCALATE instead of editing.
- Commit at every coherent stopping point. Do not leave finished work sitting
  uncommitted in the working tree.

## Lane boundaries
- Files you may edit: `modes/jarvis/**`, `shared/google_client.py`,
  `shared/crypto.py`, `MOBILE_API_GUIDE.md`, `docs/JARVIS_PLAN.md`.
- Files you may NOT edit without an ESCALATE + explicit go-ahead recorded in
  the task: `main.py`, `shared/db.py`, `shared/auth.py`, `shared/agent_loop.py`,
  `shared/confirm_match.py`, `shared/spoken_readback.py`, `AGENTS.md`,
  `.cursor/rules/*`, `migrations/*`. These are Jack's lane (see OWNERSHIP.md);
  a needed change there is a written proposal, not an edit.
- `shared/confirm_match.py` and `shared/spoken_readback.py` are verbatim ports
  from the reference. Never "improve" them.

## Carried over from 00-core (the ones that keep coming up)
- This repo is PUBLIC: no secrets, no real personal data, anywhere. Env vars
  via `os.environ` only. Never commit `.env`.
- The Confirm Gate fronts every irreversible action. A code path that sends,
  creates, or reschedules without a confirmed pending_action is a critical bug.
- The API contract (10-api-contract.mdc) is frozen. Additive changes need
  Jack's approval BEFORE implementation, and docs update in the same commit
  as the code.
- ESCALATE early. "I'm not sure" beats a confident guess in someone else's lane.
